commitResults.messageBody:
There are no remedial action for default statements used under switch
statements

Amended the classes above in the commit: DateTime, Parser, TaskList
In DateTime:
* If we are to create a DateTime from storage and a WrongInputException
is thrown, that means that there is data corruption in the file storage
That is a invalid file format was stored. Thus we use assert to
terminate the program since the file is no longer safe to work with.

In Parser:
* Upon hitting the default case which means after parsing a command,
it did not throw an exception however it is invalid means that the
system has failed to detect an invalid command, the program should
terminate to prevent any further actions

In TaskList:
* We assert to check if the storage data is corrupted, that is if there
is even the minimum amount of data to form a task (Task name, status
and type). Programme should terminate to prevent wrong exception
message for the problem
* Assert in default statement since it is a invalid task however it was
created and stored , data is corrupted, should stop execution of program
* Assert in creating task List because we return null in ParseTask
This results in problematic null pointer exception that
could possibly be caught and given the wrong description.
Program is no longer functioning as it should be, should terminate

The asserts are done as a way to deal with highly unlikely but
theoretically possible situations that could cause multiple exceptions
and code functionality to stop working as intended. The strategy to
recover from this situation is to terminate since clearing data file
should not be called by default

commitResults.messageTitle: Clean up code to better reflect code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
Had consistency issue with guard clauses (some methods implementing
guard clauses while other using if for happy path)

Amended them to have guard clauses and no default branches are used,
that is else statements are removed, changed to if else or if statements
as guard clauses.

Additionally, there was unused methods, parameters in constructors and
classes

Remove File Manager class which no methods were implemented, changed
constructors of several classes like Deadline, Event, SearchEngine
where parameters were used, removing the redundant fields as well

This was done to clean up code that was unused

Apply DRY to prevent code duplication. Code that was defined
twice was condensed, this was seen in task Validator in deadline and
Event class

Apply SLAP in Parser class to achieve single level abstraction as well
as same abstraction levels

Magic Number like offsets to determine taskName for ToDos, Deadline,
Events were declared as final static constants in their respective class

This increases readability in terms of how we are searching for taskName

Deep Nesting was also checked for, there is no loops that is more than
2 nest deep as a general guideline

Long methods are kept minimal, even though impossible to keep to a hard
constraint of 30 lines for some methods like parsing

Code quality in total was cleaned up for all classes and scanned through
Code remains functional after changes as well
